Part 1:
To start , first download node js >> Then install Visual studio code
Then in some drive create a project folder >> Then open the folder in Vs code editor
Then install playwright through vs terminal by command >> npm init playwright@latest
Then installer will ask about the language >> typescript/javascript
Then it ask you about test directory >> where will you store your tests
Then installer asks about github action wokflow and then it asks you about the browsers to be installed
Then all the folders and package.json file gets saved in your project directory >> also one demo example file gets saved for syntax and format 

Part 2: Playwright time travel/ Test runner

This is a UI mode in which you can see your test and debug your test 
this can be installed by terminal >> npx plarwright test --ui
or 
Can be installed by extensions >> go to settngs in vs code >> goto extensions and search for playwright test and click install >> it is developed by microsfot to monitor our test 

Then we have to install playwright test through terminal to our project >> command >> npx install playwright --same --dev
Then install playwright test to write our tests >> command >> npx install @playwright/test --same --dev 
Note: both versions of playwright and playwright test should be same in package.json file
Then we have to initialize typescript as well >> command >> npx install typescript --save --dev
Then run command >> npx tsc --init

IMP: To run a test in playwright use command: >> npx playwright test testname.spec.ts
